Could you try running the `window` examlpe in https://github.com/rust-windowing/glutin?

This is the patch you need to apply to disable decorations for the example:

```diff
diff --git a/glutin_examples/examples/window.rs b/glutin_examples/examples/window.rs
index f7da6c4..9ae551b 100644
--- a/glutin_examples/examples/window.rs
+++ b/glutin_examples/examples/window.rs
@@ -7,7 +7,7 @@ use glutin::ContextBuilder;
 
 fn main() {
     let el = EventLoop::new();
-    let wb = WindowBuilder::new().with_title("A fantastic window!");
+    let wb = WindowBuilder::new().with_title("A fantastic window!").with_decorations(false);
 
     let windowed_context =
         ContextBuilder::new().build_windowed(wb, &el).unwrap();
```

You can apply patches using `git apply patch.file` and then run the example using `cargo run --example window`.
